<name>BODY ELECTRICAL</name>
<section id="1002P_S001H" variety="S001H">
<name>METER</name>
<ttl id="1002P_S001H_739WU_T00GY" variety="T00GY">
<name>ENGINE OIL PRESSURE SWITCH</name>
<para id="RM0000014W700AX" category="G" type-id="8000T" name-id="ME04P-11" from="200601">
<name>ON-VEHICLE INSPECTION</name>
<subpara id="RM0000014W700AX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM0000014W700AX_01_0001" proc-id="RM0250U___0000CL400000">
<ptxt>INSPECT ENGINE OIL PRESSURE SWITCH ASSEMBLY</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Disconnect the connector from the oil pressure switch assembly. </ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>With the switch still installed, measure the resistance between the terminal of the engine oil pressure switch and engine ground.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard resistance</title>
<subtitle>Engine stopped</subtitle>
<specitem>
<ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt>
</specitem>
<subtitle>Engine idling</subtitle>
<specitem>
<ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<atten4>
<ptxt>If the value is not as specified, replace the engine oil pressure switch.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
</servcat>
</pub>
